Sentencas: The performance of SmBaCoFeO5+delta (SBCF)-xCe(0.9)Gd(0.1)O(1.95) (GDC) (x = 0, 10, 30, 50, 60, wt%) composite cathodes has been investigated for their potential utilization in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The powder X-ray diffraction (XRD), thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) and electrochemical property measurements are employed to study the materials.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The XRD results prove that there is no serious reaction between SBCF and GDC oxides even at 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion behavior shows that the TEC value of SBCF cathode decreases greatly with GDC addition.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The addition of GDC to SBCF cathode further reduces the polarization resistance.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An electrolytesupported fuel cell is prepared using SBCF-50GDC as cathode and NiO-GDC (65:35 by weight) as anode.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell generates good performance with the maximum power density of 691 mW cm(-2), 503 mW cm(-2) and 337 mW cm-2 at 800 degrees C, 750 degrees C and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Preliminary results indicate that SBCF-50GDC is especially promising as a cathode for ITSOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBaCoFeO5+δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
